 Purpose:
Relational database providing persistent storage for Gitea (Git repositories, users, issues, pull requests).

Access Information:
- URL: N/A (internal database - no web interface)
- Port(s): (internal only - not exposed externally)
- Location (VM): apps.lab.local
- Container/Service Name: postgres

Credentials:
- Admin Username: postgres
- Admin Password Location: Stored in Vaultwarden

Technical Details:
- Database: PostgreSQL 16
- Configuration Files: /opt/docker/postgres/ (if custom config exists)
- Data Location: /opt/docker/postgres-data/ (or Docker volume 'postgres-data')
- Log Location: docker logs postgres

Common Operations:

Restart:
docker compose restart postgres

View Logs:
docker logs postgres -f

Check Status:
docker ps | grep postgres
docker exec postgres pg_isready

Backup:
docker exec postgres pg_dump -U gitea gitea > /opt/backups/gitea-db-$(date +%Y%m%d).sql

Dependencies:
- Requires: None (standalone database)
- Required by: Gitea (cannot function without database)

Notes:
- Contains Gitea database named “gitea”
- Critical data - backup regularly
- Do NOT delete without backing up first
- Restore: docker exec -i postgres psql -U gitea gitea < backup.sql
